SWIID Version 9.2 is available!

Frederick Solt

2021-12-22

Version 9.2 of the SWIID is now available! This new release:

  • adds to its source data 3834 new Ginis since version 9.1, including newly available LIS data on Egypt, Germany, Lithuania, Mexico, the Netherlands, Russia, Slovenia, Spain, the United States, Georgia, Switzerland, Australia, Austria, Colombia, Paraguay, Polad, Russia (yes, again!), and Vietnam; and

  • includes estimates of market and disposable income inequality for 121 more country-years than version 9.1.

For more details, you can check out the all the R and Stan code used to generate the estimates in the SWIID GitHub repository. As always, I encourage users of the SWIID to email me with their comments, questions, and suggestions.
